I'm glad you got it working. And i did mean an AND gate. <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logic_gate">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logic_gate</a><!-- m --><br /><br />If you used an OR gate of two /CE signals then the chip would only enable when BOTH signals were active meaning that you're never activate the chip because the / symbol means active low meaning 0.<br /><br />Check out this Mega Man X3 hack. <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.romhacking.net/forum/index.php?topic=11130.0">http://www.romhacking.net/forum/index.php?topic=11130.0</a><!-- m --><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.romhacking.net/hacks/888/">http://www.romhacking.net/hacks/888/</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1726">MottZilla</a> — Sat Jul 06, 2013 10:40 am</p><hr />
